# UI/UX Bug Reports


---

## 1. Button Alignment Issue

**Browser:** Chrome 120, Safari  
**OS:** Windows 10, macOS  
**Device:** Desktop, Laptop  
**Page:** Contact Page  
**Type:** UI/Layout  
**Priority:** Medium  
**Severity:** Low  
**Environment:** Production  
**Reproducibility:** 100%

**Steps to Reproduce:**

1. Open contact page
2. Observe the "Submit" button position

**Actual Result:**

- Button appears offset to the right and not aligned with form fields

**Expected Result:**

- Button should be centered and properly aligned with all form input fields

**Attachments:**

- [screenshot-link.com](#)

---

## 2. Inconsistent Font Sizes

**Browser:** Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge  
**OS:** Windows 10, macOS  
**Device:** Desktop, Laptop  
**Page:** Multiple pages (Home, About, Services)  
**Type:** UI/Typography  
**Priority:** Low  
**Severity:** Low  
**Environment:** Production  
**Reproducibility:** 100%

**Steps to Reproduce:**

1. Navigate to the Home page and note the header size
2. Navigate to the About page
3. Compare header font sizes

**Actual Result:**

- Header sizes vary between 24px and 28px across different pages

**Expected Result:**

- All page headers should have consistent font size (28px)

**Attachments:**

- [screenshot-link.com](#)

---

## 3. Loading Spinner Not Centered

**Browser:** Chrome, Firefox  
**OS:** Windows 10, macOS  
**Device:** Desktop, Laptop  
**Page:** Products Page  
**Type:** UI/Layout  
**Priority:** Low  
**Severity:** Low  
**Environment:** Production  
**Reproducibility:** 100%

**Steps to Reproduce:**

1. Navigate to the products page
2. Observe loading spinner during initial page load

**Actual Result:**

- Spinner appears in the upper-left quadrant of the screen

**Expected Result:**

- Loading spinner should be centered both vertically and horizontally on the page

**Attachments:**

- [screenshot-link.com](#)

---

## 4. Navigation Menu Overlaps Content

**Browser:** Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge  
**OS:** Windows 10, macOS  
**Device:** Desktop, Laptop  
**Page:** All pages  
**Type:** UI/Layout  
**Priority:** High  
**Severity:** Medium  
**Environment:** Production  
**Reproducibility:** 100%

**Steps to Reproduce:**

1. Open the site on desktop browser
2. Resize browser window to tablet width (768px - 1024px)
3. Open the navigation menu
4. Observe the overlap with main content area

**Actual Result:**

- Navigation menu covers approximately 40% of the main content area

**Expected Result:**

- Menu should either push content to the side or appear as a proper overlay without obscuring important content elements

**Attachments:**

- [screenshot-link.com](#)

---

